  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Coordinator (Projects)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage operations of various projects (Including 24-hour operation Projects)</li>\n  <li>Needs to handle and take care of multiple projects</li>\n  <li>Activate Standby personnel or stand in for the absence of personnel in the project</li>\n  <li>Rostering for operations/ensuring KPI maintained on all the projects under their care</li>\n  <li>Visit the project sites and ensure deliverables of the project specs (Islandwide)</li>\n  <li>Monthly attendance report and work report preparation and submission with the client for the necessary approval</li>\n  <li>Invoice preparation and submission to the client for the necessary payment processing</li>\n  <li>Join the recruitment manager for the necessary project recruitment and interview arrangements.</li>\n  <li>Collect feedback on the staff performance with the client</li>\n  <li>Coordinate and arrange the needful logistics arrangement for the project.</li>\n  <li>Planning and executing project budgets.</li>\n  <li>Able to do hands-on work during the absence of the deployed project staff</li>\n  <li>Motivating and supervising assigned staff.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications and Skills Required:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Must be qualified with a relevant bachelor's degree</li>\n  <li>Able to do hands-on work (Physical work)</li>\n  <li>Able to travel to multiple locations</li>\n  <li>Able to work on rotational shifts &amp; weekends (Off Day on weekdays)</li>\n  <li>Experience in project coordination is an added advantage.</li>\n  <li>Good communication and interpersonal skills.</li>\n</ul>",
